[[Image:DOMC logo.png|right|140px]] The '''Defense of Marriage Coalition''' (sometimes styled '''Oregon Defense of Marriage Coalition''' to distinguish itself from similar organizations in other states) is a citizens' political organization support the definition of marriage as the union of one man and one woman. It was organized in 2004<ref>http://www.christianpost.com/news/defense-of-marriage-coalition-to-file-injunction-against-oregon-2389</ref> by the [[Oregon Family Council]]<ref>http://www.cnnw.com/articles/articles4-04-1.html</ref> as a campaign first to place [[Oregon Ballot Measure 36 (2004)]] before the voters by [[Initiative|initiative petition]], and then once signatures were collected, as a campaign for its passage. The organization formed a coalition of 1,500 churches<ref>http://chronicle.augusta.com/stories/2004/06/19/rel_419509.shtml</ref> and collected a record 244,000 signatures to place the amendment on the ballot.<ref>http://www.bpnews.net/printerfriendly.asp?ID=18618</ref>
