'''''The Perils of "Privilege": Why Injustice Can’t Be Solved by Accusing Others of Advantage''''' is a 2017 non-fiction book by [[Phoebe Maltz Bovy]].<ref>{{cite web|work=[[Commentary (magazine)|Commentary]]|url=https://www.commentarymagazine.com/articles/playing-the-percentages/|title=Playing the Percentages|author=Zelinsky, Nathaniel|date=April 7, 2017}}</ref><ref name=WP>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/book-party/wp/2017/03/23/the-last-thing-on-privilege-youll-ever-need-to-read/|work=[[The Washington Post]]|title=The last thing on ‘privilege’ you’ll ever need to read|author=Lozada, Carlos|date=March 23, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|work=[[The New York Times]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/12/opinion/sunday/identity-politics-white-men.html|title=I’m a White Man. Hear Me Out.|authorlink=Frank Bruni|author=Bruni, Frank|date=August 12, 2017}}</ref>
==Overview== A look into the concept of "privilege" and how it affects progressive politics and that accusing others of unearned advantages does nothing to address inequality and perhaps only makes things worse.
